<paragraph id="960336CB6A60FFC5A12DEC98FDAD271B" blockId="2.[369,574,238,259]" box="[369,574,238,259]" pageId="2" pageNumber="262">
<heading id="CD4B81A76A60FFC5A12DEC98FDAD271B" box="[369,574,238,259]" centered="true" fontSize="9" level="2" pageId="2" pageNumber="262" reason="2">
THE 
<taxonomicName id="51BC4D486A60FFC5A1F7EC98FDAD271B" authority="PUZZLE" box="[427,574,238,259]" class="Arachnida" family="Sironidae" genus="Siro" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A4C8EAD96A60FFC5A1F7EC98FE72271B" box="[427,481,238,259]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="262">SIRO</emphasis>
PUZZLE
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="960336CB6A60FFC5A0F8ED54FE0822F5" blockId="2.[164,779,290,1321]" pageId="2" pageNumber="262">
Since the first description of the species 
<taxonomicName id="51BC4D486A60FFC5A2D8ED54FEDE274C" authority="Latreille, 1804" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1804" class="Arachnida" family="Sironidae" genus="Siro" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubens">
<emphasis id="A4C8EAD96A60FFC5A2D8ED54FC98272E" box="[644,779,290,311]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="262">Siro rubens</emphasis>
Latreille, 1804
</taxonomicName>
(first described cyphophthalmid) until today, 24 recent species and subspecies have been described in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="51BC4D486A60FFC5A192ED08FE6D278A" box="[462,510,382,403]" class="Arachnida" family="Sironidae" genus="Siro" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A4C8EAD96A60FFC5A192ED08FE6D278A" box="[462,510,382,403]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="262">Siro</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A somewhat greater number of Cyphophthalmi species is known in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="51BC4D486A60FFC5A0ADEDCDFED727C9" authorityName="Hirst" authorityYear="1926" box="[241,324,443,464]" class="Arachnida" family="Pettalidae" genus="Rakaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A4C8EAD96A60FFC5A0ADEDCDFED727C9" box="[241,324,443,464]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="262">Rakaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="EEAB765B6A60FFC5A1D0EDCDFDB627C8" box="[396,549,443,465]" name="New Zealand" pageId="2" pageNumber="262">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="EEAB765B6A60FFC5A23EEDCDFD5D27C8" box="[610,718,443,465]" name="Australia" pageId="2" pageNumber="262">Australia</collectingCountry>
– 29 taxa (
<bibRefCitation id="F22D4B3A6A60FFC5A0B5EDAFFE1527F6" author="Giribet G" box="[233,390,473,495]" pageId="2" pageNumber="262" pagination="49 - 76" refId="ref23561" refString="Giribet G. 2000. Catalogue of the Cyphophthalmi of the world (Arachnida, Opiliones). Revista Iberica de Aracnologia 2: 49 - 76." type="journal article" year="2000">Giribet, 2000</bibRefCitation>
), and the genus 
<taxonomicName id="51BC4D486A60FFC5A20CEDAFFD5927F7" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1874" box="[592,714,473,494]" class="Arachnida" family="Stylocellidae" genus="Stylocellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A4C8EAD96A60FFC5A20CEDAFFD5927F7" box="[592,714,473,494]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="262">Stylocellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from South-East Asia – 24 species (
<bibRefCitation id="F22D4B3A6A60FFC5A25BED8EFD362417" author="Giribet G" box="[519,677,504,526]" pageId="2" pageNumber="262" pagination="1 - 9" refId="ref23589" refString="Giribet G. 2002. Stylocellus ramblae, a new stylocellid (Opiliones, Cyphophthalmi) from Singapore, with a discussion of the family Stylocellidae. Journal of Arachnology 30: 1 - 9." type="journal article" year="2002">Giribet, 2002</bibRefCitation>
). In contrast to these two genera (and all Cyphophthalmi genera known to date), the genus 
<taxonomicName id="51BC4D486A60FFC5A21EEE43FDE12453" box="[578,626,565,586]" class="Arachnida" family="Sironidae" genus="Siro" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A4C8EAD96A60FFC5A21EEE43FDE12453" box="[578,626,565,586]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="262">Siro</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has far surpassed the distribution areas of other genera. This genus as circumscribed ‘traditionally’ is distributed across wider areas of two continents – America: the west coast of North America, the Appalachian Mountains in eastern North America (
<bibRefCitation id="F22D4B3A6A60FFC5A267EEB8FD5A24FD" author="Shear WA" box="[571,713,718,740]" pageId="2" pageNumber="262" pagination="1 - 34" refId="ref24390" refString="Shear WA. 1980. A review of the Cyphophthalmi of the United States and Mexico, with a proposed reclassification of the suborder (Arachnida, Opiliones). American Museum Novitates 2705: 1 - 34." type="journal article" year="1980">Shear, 1980</bibRefCitation>
) and Europe: Western Europe – an area in south-eastern 
<collectingCountry id="EEAB765B6A60FFC5A0F8EF7AFF652538" box="[164,246,780,801]" name="France" pageId="2" pageNumber="262">France</collectingCountry>
, the southern and south-eastern Alps, the Balkan Peninsula to its southernmost points and south-east to western parts of 
<collectingCountry id="EEAB765B6A60FFC5A246EF3EFD0D2547" box="[538,670,840,862]" name="Turkey" pageId="2" pageNumber="262">
Asia 
<taxonomicName id="51BC4D486A60FFC5A205EF3EFD0D2547" authority="(Gruber, 1969)" baseAuthorityName="Gruber" baseAuthorityYear="1969" box="[601,670,840,862]" class="Arachnida" family="Sironidae" genus="Parasiro" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minor">Minor</taxonomicName>
</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="F22D4B3A6A60FFC5A2EFEF3EFF4E2564" author="Gruber J" pageId="2" pageNumber="262" pagination="75 - 88" refId="ref23625" refString="Gruber J. 1969. Weberknechte der Familien Sironidae und Trogulidae aus der Turkei (Opiliones, Arachnida). Revue de la Faculte des Sciences de la Universite d'Istanbul 34: 75 - 88." type="journal article" year="1969">Gruber, 1969</bibRefCitation>
), and north-east to the northern Carpathian Mountains (
<bibRefCitation id="F22D4B3A6A60FFC5A168EFF0FE5C2585" author="Masan P" box="[308,463,902,924]" pageId="2" pageNumber="262" pagination="650" refId="ref24259" refString="Masan P. 1998. First record of Siro carpaticus (Opiliones, Cyphophthalmi, Sironidae) from Slovakia. Biologia, Bratislava 53: 650." type="journal article" year="1998">Mašan, 1998</bibRefCitation>
). Such a distribution of a genus is surprisingly unusual for relict endogean species of limited dispersal capability, such as Cyphophthalmi undoubtedly are, and results from neglecting obvious generic boundaries amongst sironids. Analysis of sequence data from three nuclear and two mitochondrial genes (
<bibRefCitation id="F22D4B3A6A60FFC5A27AE84BFC97224A" author="Boyer S &amp; Karaman I &amp; Giribet G" box="[550,772,1085,1107]" pageId="2" pageNumber="262" pagination="554 - 567" refId="ref23442" refString="Boyer S, Karaman I, Giribet G. 2005. The genus Cyphophthalmus (Arachnida, Opiliones, Cyphophthalmi) in Europe: a phylogenetic approach to Balkan Peninsula biogeography. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 36: 554 - 567." type="journal article" year="2005">
Boyer 
<emphasis id="A4C8EAD96A60FFC5A227E848FD20224B" box="[635,691,1085,1107]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="262">et al.</emphasis>
, 2005
</bibRefCitation>
) shows the monophyletic clade of Balkan sironids not to be directly related to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="51BC4D486A60FFC5A275E80DFDCA2289" box="[553,601,1147,1168]" class="Arachnida" family="Sironidae" genus="Siro" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A4C8EAD96A60FFC5A275E80DFDCA2289" box="[553,601,1147,1168]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="262">Siro</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and is another argument for separation of all Balkan and 
<collectingCountry id="EEAB765B6A60FFC5A2D0E8EFFC9922B6" box="[652,778,1177,1199]" name="Turkey" pageId="2" pageNumber="262">Asia Minor</collectingCountry>
species in the resurrected genus 
<taxonomicName id="51BC4D486A60FFC5A214E8CEFC9822D4" authorityName="JOSEPH" authorityYear="1868" box="[584,779,1208,1229]" class="Arachnida" family="Sironidae" genus="Cyphophthalmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A4C8EAD96A60FFC5A214E8CEFC9822D4" box="[584,779,1208,1229]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="262">Cyphophthalmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="F22D4B3A6A60FFC5A0F0E8A0FEFC22F5" author="Karaman I" box="[172,367,1238,1260]" pageId="2" pageNumber="262" pagination="1 - 9" refId="ref24001" refString="Karaman I. 2005 a. Evidence of spermatophores in Cyphophthalmi (Arachnida, Opiliones). Revue suisse de Zoologie 112: 1 - 9." type="journal article" year="2005">
<collectingRegion id="5478F8296A60FFC5A0F0E8A0FE8822F2" box="[172,283,1238,1259]" country="Turkey" name="Karaman" pageId="2" pageNumber="262">Karaman</collectingRegion>
, 2005a
</bibRefCitation>
, b).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
